The paper deals with the construction and weight distribution of binary linear codes, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The mention of secret sharing schemes also suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.DM) and computer security (cs.CC). Finally, the use of these codes in space communications and data storage implies a possible link to computer networks (cs.CY).
